<title>Roberto Bayardo's home page</title>

<h1>Roberto Bayardo</h1>

<b> Ph.D. Candidate </b> (Expected completion date: Fall 96!!!) <br>  <b>

 <a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/">Department of Computer Sciences</a> <br>
 <a href="http://www.utexas.edu/">The University of Texas at Austin </a> </b> <br> <br>
 Currently I am also working for <a href="http://www.mcc.com/"> MCC</a> within the <a href="http://www.mcc.com/projects/infosleuth/"> InfoSleuth</a> project. <p>

<hr size=3>
<h3> Research Interests </h3>
<ul> 
<li> Query processing
<li> Active and expert database systems
<li> Data mining 
<li> Constraint satisfaction
</ul>

My thesis advisor is <a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/miranker"> Prof. Daniel P. Miranker</a>. <br>

Some of my <a href= "http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/bayardo/papers.html"> research papers</a> are on-line,
along with a <a href = "http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/bayardo/papers.html#toolkit"> toolkit</a> for generating
and solving exceptionally hard SAT instances. <br>

